The Benue State Government has confirmed the death of Dr Emmanuel Saleh Ikwulono, the state’s commissioner of Health and Human Services. The Commissioner for Information, Culture and Tourism, Rt Hon Ngunan Addingi made the confirmation in a statement made Available to DAILY POST on Thursday. The statement also said that details of interments will be announced soon. “The Benue State Government wishes to announce with great sorrow the sad departure of our beloved, Dr Emmanuel Saleh Ikwulono, the Benue State Commissioner of Health and Human Services. “Our heart goes out to the family and the entire state at this time. “May his gentle soul rest in peace. Details of interments will be announced soon,” the statement said.